description: Foundry: Sorkin Type Co Inder is a low contrast workhorse sans serif text face design. It was inspired by German art noveau style lettering and the Amsterdam School of architecture. Inder has been carefully adjusted to the restrictions of the screen. Inder can be used in a wide range of sizes. Source files are available from Google Code. To contribute to the project contact Eben Sorkin.
